  "type": "feat",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Starting at 3rd level</strong></span>, you've mastered the omni-shield. As a bonus action, create a large kinetic shield out of your omni-tool that lasts one minute. You can end Omni-shield at any point as a free action.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">While Omni-Shield is deployed you cannot use another omni-* melee weapon. Instead, gain the following:</p>\n<ul style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.8em; padding-left: 1.4em; list-style-position: outside; list-style-image: initial;\">\n<ul style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.8em; padding-left: 1.4em; list-style-position: outside; list-style-image: initial;\">\n<li style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; break-inside: avoid;\">+1 AC.</li>\n<li style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; break-inside: avoid;\">If a creature within 2m of you is attacked, you may use your reaction to impose disadvantage on that attack.</li>\n<li style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; break-inside: avoid;\">As an attack action, you may make a melee attack roll. On a hit, deal 1d12 bludgeoning damage. You may shove a hit creature backward 2m.</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">Once you use this feature, you must finish a short or long rest before you can use it again.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Starting at 14th level</strong></span>, you can transform your omni-shield into a fire shield or cryo shield.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\"><strong style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Fire Shield</strong>. Gain all the benefits of Omni-Shield. In addition, a target hit by a Fire Shield attack takes 3d10 fire damage. This damage detonates primed targets, but you are immune to any detonating effects.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\"><strong style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Cryo Shield</strong>. Gain all the benefits of Omni-Shield. In addition, a target hit by a Cryo Shield attack takes 1d8 cold damage and must succeed on a DC 13 Strength saving throw or become until the end its next turn.</p>",
